{%- comment -%}
  dev-stars — shared inline-SVG star rating.

  Replaces the Unicode ★ (U+2605) glyph — which is absent from Public Sans, falls back to a
  system font and so varies across platforms — with one canonical vector. This is the
  exact-fidelity fix the Promo/rating-bar spec asks for ("render the stars as inline SVGs
  rather than font glyphs, which vary across platforms").

  The Figma file ships NO star vector to export (its rating rows are literal ★ text), so this
  clean 5-point star is an AUTHORISED substitution — not a Figma export. One component feeds
  every rating (promo bar, featured product, PDP buy box, reviews) so they can never disagree.

  Params:
    rating {number}  filled amount, 0..max        (default: max — a full row)
    max    {number}  number of stars              (default: 5)
    size   {number}  star edge in px              (default: 16)
    gap    {number}  space between stars in px    (default: 2)
    color  {string}  filled-star colour           (default: currentColor)
    track  {string}  empty-star colour            (default: rgba(0,0,0,0.15))
    label  {string}  accessible name — when set the group is role="img"; else aria-hidden
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign star_max = max | default: 5
  assign star_rating = rating | default: star_max
  assign star_size = size | default: 16
  assign star_gap = gap | default: 2
  assign star_fill = color | default: 'currentColor'
  assign star_track = track | default: 'rgba(0,0,0,0.15)'

  assign star_pct = star_rating | times: 100.0 | divided_by: star_max
  if star_pct > 100
    assign star_pct = 100
  elsif star_pct < 0
    assign star_pct = 0
  endif

  comment
    A regular 5-point star drawn with straight lines only — sharp points, NO rounded corners.
    Outer radius 11 / inner radius ~4.2 (the regular {5/2} ratio).

    The viewBox starts at y = -1.05, and that offset is load-bearing. The path runs y 1 -> 20.9,
    so it is 19.9 tall inside a 24 box and its centre is at 10.95, not 12 — a star sitting 1.05
    units high in its own box. Every consumer centres the BOX (align-items: center), so that bias
    came straight through as ink ~0.6px above the text it sits beside at 13px, which is what made
    the drawer's rating row read as misaligned. Offsetting the viewBox by (24 - 19.9) / 2 - 1
    re-centres the box on the ink without touching the path or the rendered size.

    Horizontally the path is already symmetric (1.54 -> 22.46, centre 12), so x stays 0.
  endcomment
  capture star_svg
    echo '<svg viewBox="0 -1.05 24 24" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="M12 1L14.47 8.6L22.46 8.6L15.99 13.3L18.47 20.9L12 16.2L5.53 20.9L8.01 13.3L1.54 8.6L9.53 8.6Z"/></svg>'
  endcapture
-%}
<span
  class="dev-stars"
  style="--dev-stars-size:{{ star_size }}px;--dev-stars-gap:{{ star_gap }}px;--dev-stars-fill:{{ star_fill }};--dev-stars-track:{{ star_track }};--dev-stars-pct:{{ star_pct }}%;"
  {%- if label != blank %} role="img" aria-label="{{ label | escape }}"{% else %} aria-hidden="true"{% endif -%}
>
  <span class="dev-stars__row dev-stars__row--track">
    {%- for i in (1..star_max) -%}{{ star_svg }}{%- endfor -%}
  </span>
  <span class="dev-stars__row dev-stars__row--fill">
    {%- for i in (1..star_max) -%}{{ star_svg }}{%- endfor -%}
  </span>
</span>
